name: Sterling Pierce Sanders

social_posts.post_text:
Another 365 days around the sun, that makes 40 in total. What a ride it’s been. Thank you all for the time, effort, energy and contributions big and small you’ve made to my life, hope only I can return it more than 10x in the next 40. Celebrating another Happy #Birthday a world away. See you on the other side!
—
Happy new year! May the best of your todays, be the worst of your tomorrows!

“The greatest power on Earth is the magnificent power we all of us possess—the power of the human [mind].” “For there is nothing either good or bad, but thinking makes it so.” From power comes freedom. So, free yourself of the constraints, use it to “Seize the time—live now! Make now always the most precious time. [Because it will not] come again.” And if you can manage it, do with a clever distaste of seriousness.
—
Two fun facts about me, Shakespeare is my favorite writer because I love the value and economy of meaning in his word use—big fan of slow and fast intrinsic, explicit, and enigmatic multi-entendres—and I happen to name all the important things in my life after cultural experiences that have affected me in profound or frivolous ways. 

With that said, let me introduce, Xavier. Xavier Deathstar. She’s a 2022 @teslamotors #ModelX #Plaid delivered last June as an early #Birthday present to self. Thanks #tesla she’s been a wild ride!

Will leave the theory-crafting of the meaning and relevance of the name up to you all, the combined wit of the internet is a marvel to behold after all. ;) But I’ve had so much fun making awesome things last year, I’m usually the type to shoot for the stars, so I’m happy to make this my final creative sign off to 2022. #ontothenext
—
Happy birthday tooooo meeeeeeeeee! …… aaaannndddd MANY MMMOOOORRREEEE!
—

Some say I have too much fun, I say, that’s frankly impossible. ;) But maybe I’m simply the type that likes to make the “impossible” reality? 😁

Waves beat against rock as emotions rise. Strong, unyielding, unpredictable. An unwieldy power that make vulnerable any opponent. A power from which some run and hide, some battle through gritted teeth, with sword and shield, and some rare few embrace the challenge with excited grins in attempt to make life there, on those infinite seas, to lead others on the journey of a lifetime for greener pastures. 

Storms like waves come and go, but the fearless are the ones who remain standing. 

Freedom is not for the faint of heart, it is full of uncertainty, discomfort, trial, and tribulation; it takes hard work, energy, care, and optimism. Find your hope in the vulnerability. Free yourself.

It didn’t occur to me until I was boarding my plane from Doha last night that I would be flying into New York on the morning September 11th, 2023. Just in time in fact to observe a moment of silence with all of JFK. Vivid memories of that day came flooding back and how it shifted my entire perception of reality.

I was reminded of how important it is to take care of your loved ones, to tell them what you think, how you feel, what you think of them, and where you stand all the time. To hug them a little tighter, every chance you get.

I was reminded of how the lines of division between us, we created, and given the opportunity, when the going gets tough, it’s our fellow women and men beside us which hold us together. To accomplish great things, to be better, and do better each day. 

Head up, eyes forward. Never Forget.
—
📸 #sterlingsanders @sterlingsanders

The arrival of my birthday always marks the setting sun of another year well spent. It’s a time in which I find myself gratefully reminiscing in a futile attempt to show full appreciation of all the experiences that have come to pass in the last 365. For the friends, the love, the laughter, the smiles, but most importantly the creation of indelible memories manifested of perfect moments with those that matter most. And to all of you I say thank you. 

As I take my last bow, I’ll leave you with my final toast of the year:. Whatever you do, wherever you are, or who you’re with, make the most of it, each and every moment. See you all on the other side. Happy New Year!
